-- Golfer Bob Charles Receives New Zealand's Highest Honor in New Year List
-- B y   C h r i s   B o u r k e
-- 2010-12-30T21:19:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/golfer-bob-charles-receives-new-zealand-s-highest-honor-in-new-year-list.html
  New Zealand  golf champion  Bob
Charles  has been awarded the highest accolade in the country’s
annual New Year honors list.  The 74 year-old Charles was appointed to the Order of New
Zealand, a group limited to 20 living New Zealanders, according
to the Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet’s  website .
The award recognizes “outstanding service to the Crown and
people of New Zealand,” and included mountaineer Edmund Hillary
prior to his death in 2008.  The left-handed golfer won more than 60 international
tournaments in his career and was knighted in 1999, according to
Television New Zealand’s  website . He became the first left-
hander to win a major championship, with a victory at the
British Open in 1963, according to The Open website.  To contact the reporter for this story:
